World Bank to Give Malawi $84.7 Million for Power Transmission, Times Says

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-06-30T06:18:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/world-bank-to-give-malawi-84-7-million-for-power-transmission-times-says.html
The  World Bank  will give the
Electricity Supply Corp. of Malawi, the nation’s electricity
utility, $84.7 million to help boost transmission capacity, the
Daily Times reported, citing the bank’s country manager, Sandra
Bloemenkamp.  Bloemenkamp said $65.4 million would be a grant and the
remaining $19.3 million a loan, the Blantyre-based newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  